CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kmalloc(sizeof(*inode->inotify_data)...) over kmalloc(sizeof(struct inotify_inode_data)...)
#116: FILE: drivers/char/inotify.c:472:
+		inode->inotify_data = kmalloc(sizeof(struct inotify_inode_data),

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

